**Diag Parser v3 is here!**

I'm excited to share a major new release of the Diag Parser webapp — a complete rewrite from vanilla JS to React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind, all running inside a DSS webapp (no Code Studios required).

**What's new:**

**Compare Mode** — Upload two diagnostic files and see what changed between environments. Side-by-side deltas for health scores, system info, settings, and collections (users, projects, clusters, plugins). Great for troubleshooting "what changed?" questions.

**Health Score** — Get an at-a-glance health assessment of your instance with category breakdowns and actionable recommendations. Automatically detects issues like low file limits, EOL Python versions, memory over-provisioning, and more.

**Directory Tree Visualization** — Explore your datadir structure with an interactive tree view. Drill down into any folder to find what's eating disk space.

**Memory Analysis** — Validates cgroup limits and JEK allocations with color-coded health indicators.

**Dark Mode** — Easy on the eyes, toggle between light and dark themes.

**Redesigned UI** — Fresh visual design with improved layouts and a cleaner navigation experience.

**More Info & Performance** — Additional details now surfaced including node ID, install ID, and R environments. Even faster than v2.

All feature requests from Airtable have been implemented. As with any major rewrite, there may be some bugs lurking — please send bug reports my way, and feature requests are always welcome!
